<h1>Introduction to Exams</h1>

<p>BibleOL offers the option for creating and taking exams. While each instructor can create exams for students, institutions can use the exam feature to build exams that can be used as qualifiers for incoming students or as standardized exams that departments use for their courses.</p>

<ul>
	<li>If you are a student at Andrews University and preparing to take the <strong>final exam</strong> for the Hebrew II course (<span style="color:red; font-weight:bold;">OTST552</span>), go <strong><a href="https://learner.bible/help/show_help/AU_exam_hebrewII">here</strong></a>.</li>
	<li>If you are a student at Andrews University and preparing to take the <strong>final exam</strong> for the Intermediate Greek course (<span style="color:red; font-weight:bold;">NTST552</span>), go <strong><a href="https://learner.bible/help/show_help/AU_exam_greek">here</strong></a>.</li>
	<li>If you are an existing or prospective student at Andrews University, go <a href="https://learner.bible/help/show_help/AU_qualifier_hebrew">here</a> if you plan to sign up for the <strong>Hebrew Placement Exam</strong>.</li>
	<li>If you are a student at Andrews University and preparing to take the Hebrew Proficiency Exam required by any (<span style="color:red; font-weight:bold;">OTST exegesis course</span>), go <strong><a href="https://learner.bible/help/show_help/AU_qualifier_hebrew">here</strong></a>.</li>
</ul>
